text.section:
A policy or certificate of long-term care insurance may limit or exclude coverage of:
preexisting conditions or diseases;
mental or nervous conditions or diseases other than Alzheimer's disease;
alcohol or drug addiction;
unless otherwise provided by State or federal law, treatment provided in a government facility;
services provided by a member of the covered individual's immediate family;
services for which a charge normally is not made in the absence of insurance;
services for which benefits are available under:
Medicare or other governmental programs except Medicaid; or
a State or federal workers' compensation, employer's liability, or occupational disease law; and
illness, treatment, or medical conditions arising out of:
a declared or undeclared war or act of war;
participation in a felony, riot, or insurrection;
service in the armed forces or auxiliary units;
suicide, attempted suicide, or intentionally self-inflicted injury; or
aviation, if the insured is a passenger who does not pay a fare.
